Northmont City Schools
August 3 at 6:01 PM ¬∑

Significant update and changes regarding the restart of school for the upcoming year: Current data indicate the number of COVID-19 cases in our community are increasing and continue to impact our own employees who are essential to the reopening of school. Based on the recommendation from Public Health Dayton-Montgomery County and the Governor‚Äôs Level 3 indicator for our county we will begin the school year remotely.

Northmont will delay the beginning of the school year for students until September 1, 2020. When school begins on September 1, all students will be learning remotely. In the meantime, we will expand our ability to implement robust remote learning options with more staff training.‚Ä¶

Miami Valley Leadership Foundation
September 16, 2019 at 9:00 AM ¬∑

It's MENTORING MONDAY...

We sure do love our mentors and the positive relationships they are building with their mentees.

Meet Mike and Carson. üòä Mike and Carson became friends last year when Carson was in 3rd grade. Mike would come to the school every week to meet with Carson. They'd play games, talk about school, talk about football, etc.

However, it was hard for Mike to know if Carson really enjoyed their time together. Carson seemed like he was having fun, but Mike wasn't sure Carson cared if he came or not.

Mike remembered from his mentor training that it takes time (some longer than others) to build a positive relationship with a young person. So he continued being a consistent‚Ä¶

Northmont has partnered with YMCA to expand the high quality before and after school program to all five elementary schools for the 2019-2020 school year, that has been running very successfully at the Kleptz Early Learning Center. Open houses will be held at each elementary during the week of July 23-25. Check our website for updates throughout this summer, and see current information listed below:

ENROLLMENT PACKETS for the 2019-2020 School Year are now available at the Front Desk of the Kleptz YMCA, and at the Northmont District office at 4001 Old Salem Rd.
